{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "/nodes/vop/DASH--limit_range-1.0/DASH-limit_range-icon.svg", "type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "limit_range", "version": "1.0", "namespace": "DASH"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Limit Range"], "extent": [42, 58]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Limit, shape and repeat a range of values."], "extent": [58, 109]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [109, 124], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operation is not just useful to limit values, like ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/clamp", "type": "link", "text": ["Clamp"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/clamp.html"}, " (achievable with ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Extend"]}, " > ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Constant"]}, ") but also to set patterns beyond that range like repetitions, as well as to fine tune the transition between the limits, with a Ramp."], "extent": [124, 380]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [380, 386], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Vectors, Matrices and Arrays are treated as a package of floats and processed element-wise."], "extent": [386, 487]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Also, multidimensionals can have control signatures of multiple ranks. E.g. ", {"type": "code", "text": ["matrix2"]}, ": ", {"type": "code", "text": ["matrix2"]}, "(element-wise), ", {"type": "code", "text": ["vector2"]}, "(component-wise), ", {"type": "code", "text": ["float"]}, "(all)."], "extent": [487, 645]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [645, 657], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Value"], "extent": [657, 665], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Value to be normalized between ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Range First"]}, " and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Range Last"]}, "."], "extent": [791, 863]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "value_mp0"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Range First"], "extent": [863, 876], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Value to be mapped to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0"]}, " of the normalized range."], "extent": [1002, 1058]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "first_mp3"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Range Last"], "extent": [1058, 1070], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Value to be mapped to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["1"]}, " of the normalized range."], "extent": [1189, 1245]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "last_mp3"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Extend First/Last"], "extent": [1245, 1264], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Method used to shape the values outside of ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Range First"]}, "/", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Range Last"]}, ". The last two, ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Offset Repeat"]}, " and ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Slope"]}, " are only noticeable when using the ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["ramped"]}]}, " output and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Ramp"]}, " has a non-linear shape."], "extent": [1307, 1520]}, {"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 4, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/vop/DASH--limit_range-1.0/DASH-limit_range-help_extensions_256.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [1520, 1588]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "last_extend"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Unit First/Last"], "extent": [1588, 1605], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Keep the values normalized, which can be handy if subsequent operations require values between 0 and 1. Option is offered separately for each limit but usually makes sense to toggle them in tandem."], "extent": [1644, 1847]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "last_unit"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Ramp"], "extent": [1847, 1853], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Ramp to shape and fine tune the range\u2019s transition and its repetitions, in a non-linear way. Will only be active when the second output, ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["ramped"]}]}, ", is used. For more info on ramps check ", {"scheme": null, "value": "../../network/ramps", "type": "link", "text": ["Ramps"], "fullpath": "/network/ramps.html"}, "."], "extent": [1867, 2090]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "ramp"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Arrays Auto Resize"], "extent": [2090, 2117], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["When there are multiple input arrays, they can have different sizes. These options determine the common final size for them, as well as the fill value for those being sized up."], "extent": [2117, 2295]}, {"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Common Size"], "extent": [2295, 2308], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Common size for the multiple input arrays. ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Min"]}, " will use the smallest size, while ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Max"]}, " will use the greatest size among the input arrays."], "extent": [2339, 2484]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "array_autoresize_size"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Fill"], "extent": [2484, 2490], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Determines the fill value used for arrays being sized up. Either a ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Default"]}, " value or, if the array is not empty, its ", {"type": "em", "text": ["First"]}, " or ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Last"]}, " value."], "extent": [2524, 2672]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "array_autoresize_default"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "extent": [2672, 2682], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Description"], "extent": [2682, 2695], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["String to display info on top of the node in the network view. The pilcrow \u00b6 button enables multi-line text."], "extent": [2716, 2830]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "description"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}]}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "outputs", "container": true, "type": "outputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2830, 2839], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["ramped"]}], "extent": [2839, 2850], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Output that will make use of ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Ramp"]}, ", unlike ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["result"]}]}, "."], "extent": [2865, 2933]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "ramped"}}], "container": true}, {"type": "load_example_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "load_example", "indent": 0, "text": [" Float Manipulation"], "role": "item", "extent": [2933, 2967], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Example scene for Transform 1D, Wipe Range, Limit Range and Ramp."], "extent": [3024, 3094]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"examplefile": "/demos/vop/float_manipulation_demo.hda"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Outputs"}], "title": ["Limit Range"], "summary": ["Limit, shape and repeat a range of values."]}